MTF<br>
About your buddy;<br><br>
The giving but hesitancy to receive love, care and understanding from others, is another aspect of the Vietnam War that I believe has never been explored. <br><br>
We’re quick to give but not receive a word of thanks. Perhaps its because we all felt we only did that which was required of us, nothing more. <br><br>
Perhaps, its because we see those that suffered and died as the real heroes and because of this we all feel that any love received would be taking away from those that we feel deserved it more then we do, because they paid a higher price.<br><br>
Its not easy to receive praise for what our fellow countrymen declared was a shame.<br><br>
That is why, I believe we crave the respect and honor we can give one another but our silent presence. Thank bro, for being there.<br>
Cookie <br>

